<div class="titleblock"><div style="text-align:center; font-family: 'Georgia', serif; letter-spacing: 3px;">

<span style="font-size:30px;">'''LEVEL 112:'''</span><br>
<span style="font-size:50px;">'''CASADASTRAPHOBIA'''</span><br>

<span style="font-size:22px; letter-spacing: 5px; opacity: 0.8;">''>> Do Not Look Up At The Sky <<''</span>

</div></div>



<div class="titleblock">{{Class Gamma}}


<center>'''Level 112''' is the 113<sup>rd</sup> level of the ''Backrooms''.</center></div>



<div class="titleblock"><span style="font-size:30px;"><center>'''Overview'''</center></span></div>



{{Blurimage|file=Amicalevillefix.png|width=500px|caption=''It´s cold.''|align=center}}



<div class="titleblock"><center>
'''Level 112''' appears to be an abandoned vernacular Brazilian village, extending over 1 square kilometer.

The environment seems to have been left behind a long time ago, causing nature to reclaim what was once its own. Houses are all open and are in an advanced state of deterioration and abandonment. Even so, their structural stability is surprisingly high. One should not be overconfident, however, as the wooden ceilings are among the few fragile materials present in the level and frequently collapse upon minimal contact. The interiors are furnished, and from time to time, one can find objects of little use and rotten food.

In the village there is only one school, small and furnished. In one of the classrooms, the phrase ''"there is no salvation"'' can be found written on the blackboard, in Portuguese. It is unknown who or what wrote that message, or when.

Rarely, it is possible to find seemingly small forested regions surrounding the village, which are extremely dense; however, their vegetation and foliage lack physical collisions. For this reason, and because these specific areas appear to be [[Phenomenon 14|non-Euclidean]], it is highly recommended to avoid traversing the wooded outskirts of the village. In turn, with similar rarity, rivers and lakes exhibiting the same [[Phenomenon 14|non-Euclidean]] properties can be encountered within and around the abandoned settlement.

The level is filled with puddles of water and mud, including unusual rainfall. The environment is generally cold, with temperatures ranging from 15 to 17 degrees. A dense fog limits visibility to just a few meters, and the air is saturated with humidity and a muddy, unpleasant smell.

Although, not everything is as peaceful as it seems.

The anomalous property of this level, the one that gives it its name, is an event that occurs every few hours, during which gravity begins to reverse. During this process, the gravitational pull gradually shifts upward, toward the fog above, completing its inversion in approximately 30 seconds. Due to this, remaining in open areas becomes highly hazardous. Failure to reach adequate cover before the transition completes will result in being pulled into the upper fog layer, from which no return has been documented. The inverted gravity state persists for several hours before gradually reverting to normal. Avoid looking directly at the sky during or before a gravitational shift.

Additionally, the gravitational shift does not seem to affect the bodies of water within the level.</center></div>



<div style="max-width:900px; margin:auto; text-align:justify; line-height:1.6; font-size:15px;"><center><div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox" style="color: white;">Addendum #1</span>

<br><center>'''''What Lies Above'''''</center><br/>

<div style="max-width:900px; margin:auto; text-align:justify; line-height:1.6; font-size:15px;"><center>
I barely reached the structure before my friends were finally swallowed by the abyss above.

I heard their screams of horror slowly fade, being replaced by an overwhelming silence.

I stayed looking out the window for a few minutes, without really expecting anything to happen.

Against all odds, something happened.

The fog slowly began to disperse.

I stuck my head out the window, then I saw it.

What was above the mist.

What was waiting for us to fall up.

It was beautiful, in a way.

I felt how the wood I was standing on started to creak.

And suddenly, everything collapsed.

I fell up into the void.

But I just accepted it.

Maybe I will meet up with my friends inside its mouth.
</center>

[[File:Manta.webp|500x500px|thumb|center]]
</div></div></div>



<div class="titleblock"><center>
Minutes before a gravitational shift, sounds reminiscent of screeches, cries and screams may be heard coming from the sky. This is a sign that there will be an imminent change. The origin of these ghostly cries has not been confirmed, but legends and myths speak of massive creatures similar to clouds shaped like manta rays that float in the misty void of above with their huge mouths open, waiting for some unfortunate wanderer to fall and be devoured by them.

However, as mentioned before, this has not been possible to verify.

It has been noted that continuing to advance long enough through the forests will only cause one to return from the other side, achieving zero progress and making this an unnecessary risk. Additionally, one side of the town ends in a sea that stretches endlessly, with some empty docks. To date, nothing of interest has been found in these areas.</center></div>



<div class="titleblock"><span style="font-size:30px;"><center>'''Entrances & Exits'''</center></span></div>



<div class="titleblock"><center>Entering the level is somewhat difficult. All known entrances are listed below:</center>


* A door located on the clouds of [[Level 97]] will take one to a building of the level.
* Noclipping through a concrete wall with wet vines in [[Level 108]] will take one here.
* Noclipping the ceiling of [[Level 507]] will take one to a random location of the level.
* A vegetation-covered hallway in [[Level 810]] will take one here.
* The Green Line of [[The Metro]] can stop into the level.


<center>Likewise, exiting is also complicated. All known exits are listed below:</center>


* Following a specific path from the starting point will take one to the jungle of [[Level 110]].
* Unknown factors make the forest fade into the infested forests of [[Level 131]].
* Unknown factors make the forest darken, fading the level into the star-filled nocturnal landscape of [[Level 222]].
* Unknown factors in the shores will fade the level into the tropical paradise of [[Level 255]].
* Entering a deteriorated church will lead one to the gothic cathedrals of [[Level 313]].
* Following train tracks will lead one to one of the rail systems of [[Level 488]], [[Level 503]] or [[Level 913]].
* Submerging into a lake will pull one downward, ultimately transporting them to [[The Subwaters]].</div>



<div style="max-width:900px; margin:auto; text-align:justify; line-height:1.6; font-size:15px;"><center><div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox" style="color: white;">Addendum #2</span>

<br><center>'''''What happened to Hoer Verde?'''''</center><br/>

<div style="max-width:900px; margin:auto; text-align:justify; line-height:1.6; font-size:15px;"><center>

On February 5<sup>th</sup>, 1923, the inhabitants of a small town near the jungles of Brazil noticed that the usual daily trade shipment from the neighboring town, Hoer Verde, had not arrived. It was unusual for the ship to be late and even stranger that it did not come at all, but the villagers waited, hoping for a good reason for the delay.

However, there was none.

The next day, some villagers went to investigate what happened in Hoer Verde to cause the shipment to be delayed, but they found that the town was completely empty. Because the town was deep in the jungle, it took a long time for the news to reach the Brazilian government. But when it finally arrived, a small reconnaissance group was sent, and again, nothing was found.

Since then, no one has spoken about the matter, and the authorities have marked it as an urban legend. Some time later, Hoer Verde was removed from the newer maps, although it is still possible to find it in deprecated maps.

The people who go to the location shown on the old maps ''never return''.

Only one question remains:

[[File:Hoerverde.jpg|500x500px|thumb|center]]

''What happened to Hoer Verde?''</center>
</div></div></div></center>



